---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base
  title="Submission Guidelines — americawhat"
  description="What makes a good americawhat submission, and what not to send."
  canonicalPath="/guidelines/"
>
  <a href="/" class="back-link">&larr; back to feed</a>
  <header class="page-head">
    <div class="page-eyebrow">Legal</div>
    <h1 class="page-title">Submission Guidelines</h1>
    <p class="page-updated">Last updated: 8 July 2026</p>
  </header>

  <article class="page-card page-prose">
    <p>Saw something that made you go <em>wait, what?</em> Here's how to send a good one.</p>

    <h2>What makes a good submission</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Real and, ideally, sourced — a link, receipt, sign, screenshot, or public record.</li>
      <li>Absurd, funny, or quietly baffling. The everyday bureaucratic mysteries count.</li>
      <li>American in flavor — the HOA letter, the fee, the fine print, the local-news moment.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Please don't send</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Private personal information — full addresses, license plates, phone numbers, medical records.</li>
      <li>Anything involving minors, graphic violence, harassment, or targeting a private individual.</li>
      <li>Content you don't have the right to share.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <p>Verifiable is better. We may edit submissions for clarity, length, and tone, and not everything gets published. Items without a usable source may be marked <strong>UNVERIFIED</strong> or skipped. If you mark a submission publishable, you're giving us permission to post and caption it.</p>

    <h2>Send one</h2>
    <p>Use the <a href="/contact/">contact form</a>, or email <a href="mailto:hello@americawhat.com">hello@americawhat.com</a>.</p>
  </article>
</Base>
